      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The guy you met was a classic case of a **goblin battery**, and his car was acting exactly like a goblin trying to eat a sandwich but forgetting to chew it properly.\n\nThe issue wasn't just a failing alternator; it was a **goblin battery** that had been running on fumes for too long. When you drive, the alternator is supposed to be the boss, pumping out enough power to keep the battery charged while the engine runs. But if the alternator is weak or broken, the battery is left to do all the work alone, draining down until it's completely empty.\n\nIn this specific case, the battery light flickering or staying on even when the engine is running is the tell-tale sign. It's like a goblin who has been eating all the food in the pantry but hasn't been told to stop. The battery is still there, but it's running on fumes, and the car's electrical system is just trying to keep the lights on while the battery is slowly dying.\n\nIf you don't fix it, the battery will eventually die completely, and you'll be left with a car that won't start at all, just like a goblin who has run out of",
